      <hedline>
        <hl1>Getting Warm</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter by Jay M Pasachoff disputes William J Broad's July 5 review of two books on global warming2</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>William J. Broad's review of two books about global warming (July 5) states that ''sunlight bathes the earth and reflects back into the sky as heat.'' But it is not reflection that operates in this way, making the greenhouse effect. It is rather that the sunlight, which is mostly in the visible part of the spectrum, heats the earth's surface. That surface then radiates because it is warm, and most of that radiation is in the infrared part of the spectrum, commonly called heat radiation. So reradiation, not reflection, is the process that should have been cited. The important point is that once the energy is transformed from visible light to infrared, it can no longer pass through our atmosphere, and so is trapped.</p>
        <p>Jay M. Pasachoff</p>
        <p>Williamstown, Mass.</p>
      </block>
